<div id="main-article" class="article-content retro-folders">
<p></p><div class="indent"><em>Magic should exist to protect mankind, not to destroy it.</em><div class="indent">&mdash; <strong>Lelouch Lamperouge</strong></div></div><p><a class="urllink" href="http://www.fanfiction.net/s/9269880/1/Fairy-Without-Wings">Fairy Without Wings<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> begins with the story of Kallen Kozuki, a 17 year old mage who has been kicked out of two guilds, and witnessed the fall of a third. She's come to Fiore's town of Loreon to meet a mage consultant that might help her with her inability to control her power, which leads her to have the opportunity to join the mage guild known as Knightmare Frame. <br><br>Huh. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FairyTail" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FairyTail">Sounds familiar</a>.</p><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_1"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_1'); })</script></div></div><p>Created by draconichero21, <em>Fairy Without Wings</em> is a crossover between <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/CodeGeass" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/CodeGeass">Code Geass</a></em> and <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FairyTail" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FairyTail">Fairy Tail</a></em>. It takes the established characters from the <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/CodeGeass" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/CodeGeass">Code Geass</a></em> canon and translates them into the <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FairyTail" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FairyTail">Fairy Tail</a></em> universe with their personalities mostly intact. Lelouch is still a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MagnificentBastard" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MagnificentBastard">Magnificent Bastard</a>. Suzaku is still <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LawfulGood" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LawfulGood">Lawful Good</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LawfulStupid" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LawfulStupid">to a fault at times</a>, and Cornelia will still <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KnightTemplarBigBrother" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KnightTemplarBigBrother">tear off the head</a> of anyone who dares harm her sister <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MoralityPet" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MoralityPet">Euphemia</a>. However, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RecycledInSpace" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RecycledInSpace">now they are all mages</a>. In a guild known as Knightmare Frame, they are an ally guild to the famous - maybe even <em>in</em>famous - guild Fairy Tail, but their journey is not one of rainbows, sunshine and butterflies.<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WordOfGod" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WordOfGod">Word of God</a> is that <em>Fairy Without Wings</em> was created to show points in the mage world of Earthland that <em>should</em> come with the territory of such a world, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SlidingScaleOfIdealismVsCynicism" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SlidingScaleOfIdealismVsCynicism">but that Mashima flat out ignores or only barely hints at existing</a>. These are things that <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PayEvilUntoEvil" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PayEvilUntoEvil">Lelouch</a> would normally be seen doing on a regular basis.</p><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_2"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_2'); })</script></div></div><p>It does a surprisingly good job mixing the characters of both universes and, much like <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FairyTail" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FairyTail">Fairy Tail</a></em> itself, while the story starts with Kallen's introduction to her new guild in a parallel to Lucy, the story clearly evolves into arc based storytelling much like <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FairyTail" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FairyTail">the series proper</a>.</p><p>The <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/FanFic/TalesOfBleachUnrealSociety" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/FanFic/TalesOfBleachUnrealSociety">third</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Fanfic/SoulChess" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Fanfic/SoulChess">fanfic</a> created by draconichero to get its own tropes page and probably the best written out of the three. While <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Fanfic/SoulChess" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Fanfic/SoulChess">Soul Chess</a></em> has recently received some <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CreatorBacklash" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CreatorBacklash">Creator Backlash</a>, while still being all in all being considered a good read by most, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WordOfGod" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WordOfGod">draconichero is more satisfied with this fic thus far than the majority of</a> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Fanfic/SoulChess" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Fanfic/SoulChess">Soul Chess</a></em>. <br><br></p><hr><p></p><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_3"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_3'); })</script></div></div><h2> This Fanfiction contains examples of:</h2><p></p><hr><div class="folderlabel" onclick="toggleAllFolders();">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;open/close all folders&nbsp; </div><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder0');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Tropes A to M&nbsp;</div><div id="folder0" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ActionMom" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ActionMom">Action Mom</a>: The series is full of them in contrast to canon including: Marianne, Selina, Bisca, Kasumi, <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Nessa</span>, Sabine (as much of a monster as she is), Alice, Alysha, <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Emma</span>, and <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Atarella</span>. To say nothing then even of <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">the future characters</span> or <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> the dragon mothers</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ActorAllusion" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ActorAllusion">Actor Allusion</a>:<ul><li> When trying to remember Hibiki's name, Orochi guesses it to be <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FullMetalAlchemist" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FullMetalAlchemist">Alphonse</a>.</li><li> When <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/YuriLowenthal" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/YuriLowenthal">Suzaku</a> was born, Selina said that one of her friends wanted to name him <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Naruto" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Naruto">Sasuke</a>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AdaptationalBadass" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AdaptationalBadass">Adaptational Badass</a>: Considering the cast of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/CodeGeass" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/CodeGeass">Code Geass</a> is from a much more grounded series where no <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SuperpowerLottery" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SuperpowerLottery">Superpower Lottery</a> really existed, pretty much all of them are this. Special mention goes to Jiang Lihua aka Tianzi, who is a Moe blob in canon, but has power enough to stand on par with dragon slayers and incapacitate monsters the size of the Domus Flau.<ul><li> Jenny has graduated from simple <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MsFanservice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MsFanservice">Ms. Fanservice</a> to a genuine asskicker.</li><li> Princess Hisui is capable of fighting of her own accord.</li><li> The Rune Knights also qualify given that they're little more than mooks in canon, but have members capable of fighting on par with some of Fairy Tail's best and brightest in this story.<ul><li> This in particular is lampshaded by two of them who are annoyed by the fact that the public has such a low opinion of the rank and file of their organization as a whole.</li></ul></li><li> Mutsuki Minase was a mere <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BridgeBunnies" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BridgeBunnies">bridge bunny</a> in canon, here she's a <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Vampire-Werewolf hybrid</span> born only every 400 years.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AdaptationExpansion" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AdaptationExpansion">Adaptation Expansion</a>: In addition to the above about things Mashima either flat out ignores or only hints at existing, ever since Lelouch was <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PutOnABus" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PutOnABus">Put on a Bus</a> after the events of chapter 76 <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheBusCameBack" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheBusCameBack">though it came back</a> the series has widened itself to focus on other characters and showcase what they are capable of, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheStationsOfTheCanon" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheStationsOfTheCanon">even while Fairy Tail is trapped under the ocean thanks to Acnologia</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ADeathInTheLimelight" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ADeathInTheLimelight">A Death in the Limelight</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Poor <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheChewToy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheChewToy">Ashley Aurora</a> of Kraken's eye. In the same chapter were she does something of note, she's brutally killed by VV.</span><ul><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">In the chapter were we get to know the names and abilities of the eunuchs, they are all brutally killed by Tianzi. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AssholeVictim" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AssholeVictim">Not that anyone will miss them</a>.</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AffirmativeActionGirl" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AffirmativeActionGirl">Affirmative Action Girl</a>: There are several female Dragon Slayers, both first and second generation, to compliment Wendy.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllThereInTheManual" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllThereInTheManual">All There in the Manual</a>: You can find some brainstorm details about the fic <a class="urllink" href="http://draconichero18.deviantart.com/journal/Fanfic-Brainstorm-Fairy-Without-Wings-368727460">here<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>. The author had a second brainstorm page, but recently took it down because it was considerably spoiler heavy for things to come <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">like Marianne's death</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AlmostKiss" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AlmostKiss">Almost Kiss</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Shimon and Chelia have one of these during the Envoy From the Future arc before Orochi interrupts it</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AlwaysABiggerFish" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AlwaysABiggerFish">Always a Bigger Fish</a>: Chapter 236, and just the Guild War arc in general, plays hard ball with this trope. Grand General Karn was always a big fish and is the stronges in Fiore, but he's second-in-command to Ishgar's strongest Rune Knight, Yamato Hayabusa. Later, VV becomes so almighty <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AGodAmI" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AGodAmI">to the point of calling himself god</a>, it takes <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WildCard" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WildCard">Acnologia</a> showing up to prove that this trope is still in play. But even <em>that</em> isn't the end to this trope's usage. The immediate chapter after Acnologia shows up, <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Irene Belserion</span> shows up and proves she can hold her own against even the mighty black dragon. VV is still the smaller fish against this new arrival. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">And he winds up dying to her when he realizes just how outclassed he was</span>. However, then [<span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Irene</span> leaves the battlefield. This then allows <em>another</em> fish in the pond to start causing trouble: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">currently bonkers out of her gourd, Kallen due to trying to merge her demon soul and dragon soul together while under the effects of Mass Hysteria. Irene had kept her sedated, for lack of a better term, while she was in the area, but once she left, Kallen resumed turning the newly restored Era into the aftermath of a nuclear bomb going off</span>. And <em>even then</em>, Natsu is being utilized as the counter to this big fish by being hyped up on Etherion, courtesy of Lelouch, so he can use Dragon Force. Good god, Rube Goldberg machines are less complex than this.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AlwaysChaoticEvil" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AlwaysChaoticEvil">Always Chaotic Evil</a>: Deconstructed during the Tartaros arc with regards to demons as the arc goes out of its way to show <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThenLetMeBeEvil" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThenLetMeBeEvil">what happens when a society of one species continues to harass another just by existing</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AmazinglyEmbarrassingParents" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AmazinglyEmbarrassingParents">Amazingly Embarrassing Parents</a>: Usually Kasumi fits the bill for Kalina, but in chapter 198 she subverts this by turning out to be "cool mom" to all of Kalina's peers, especially by comparison to <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Alice and Archer Amakusa whose karaoke number makes Pyrrha go for the paper bag with eye-holes cliche to avoid being seen. Archer, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LampshadeHanging" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LampshadeHanging">knew in advance their performance would have this effect</a> and apologized to Pyrrha in advance</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnAesop" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnAesop">An Aesop</a>: Many a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FramingDevice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FramingDevice">quote</a> are like this.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AndThisIsFor" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AndThisIsFor">And This Is for...</a>: Natsu does this to a member of Omega Sphere for attacking Alzack and Bisca in chapter 7.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnyoneCanDie" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnyoneCanDie">Anyone Can Die</a>: See <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlackDudeDiesFirst" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlackDudeDiesFirst">Black Dude Dies First</a> below.<ul><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">As of chapter 114, all of the named characters in Raven Tail sans Flare and including Ivan are as good as gone. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AssholeVictim" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AssholeVictim">Not that anyone will miss them</a></span>.</li><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Uosuke from the Garou Knights has also bit the dust, but his nakama swear to avenge him from the unseen threat that plagues the Nirix arc</span>.</li><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Rufus as of the Nirix arc, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DyingMomentOfAwesome" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DyingMomentOfAwesome">but he goes out like a badass</a></span>.</li><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AgentPeacock" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AgentPeacock">Bob</a> as well, courtesy of Mordred</span>.</li><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> In Tartaros arc Babasama is also killed along with Toby and Yuka.</span></li><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> As of chapter 256, <em>All</em> members of Quattro Cerberus and most of Blue Pegasus are killed by Tartaros.</span></li><li> Chapter 260 provides probably the most savage and eye opening example of them all: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Minerva Orlando</span>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AscendedExtra" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AscendedExtra">Ascended Extra</a>: Phoenix Grave, a guild only mentioned in one of the volume extras of the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FairyTail" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FairyTail">source material</a> gets expanded into a full guild with no less than 5 members known all because one of them happens to have the same last name as Sabertooth's Minerva, so it is the author's reasonable deduction that the two are brother and sister given their father's behavior. Said brother is, again, only in the extras column. Talk about <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShownTheirWork" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShownTheirWork">showing your work</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AuthorAvatar" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AuthorAvatar">Author Avatar</a>: Alex Goldrose, mild-mannered reporter for Sorcerer Weekly.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BadassFamily" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BadassFamily">Badass Family</a>: There are several on this story:<ul><li> The Dreyar family has <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EmpoweredBadassNormal" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EmpoweredBadassNormal">Yuri</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigGood" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigGood">Makarov</a> and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShockAndAwe" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShockAndAwe">Laxus</a>. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Nessa married into the family and then divorced but she's still considered part of the Dreyar</span>. Ivan and Farah are seen as the exceptions.</li><li> The Blendy family has Sherry, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BadassAdorable" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BadassAdorable">Chelia</a> and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FourStarBadass" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FourStarBadass">Phelia</a>.</li><li> The Atrumier family has Talbomosuke, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MamaBear" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MamaBear">Kasumi</a> and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HalfHumanHybrid" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HalfHumanHybrid">Kalina</a>. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">This also includes <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheOlderImmortal" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheOlderImmortal">Ratatosk</a>.</span></li><li> The Feathermane family has <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IronLady" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IronLady">Nivea</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvilOldFolks" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EvilOldFolks">Morianna</a>, <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LadyOfWar" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LadyOfWar">Erza</a> (related to through the Knightwalker family) and Meredy (who's the most distantly related)</span>.</li><li> The Lamperouge-Vermillion family has <img src="/images/article-hreficon-ymmv.png" class="ymmv1 rounded" title="This example contains a YMMV entry. It should be moved to the YMMV tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MagnificentBastard" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MagnificentBastard">Lelouch</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ActionMom" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ActionMom">Marianne</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RealityWarper" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RealityWarper">Nunnally</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RedBaron" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RedBaron">Charles</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OurVampiresAreDifferent" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OurVampiresAreDifferent">V.V.</a> and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheStrategist" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheStrategist">Mavis</a>. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Chapter 223 reveals that <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheArchmage" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheArchmage">Zeref</a> is Mavis' husband, which means Morrigan is Lelouch's great-grandaunt</span>.</li><li> The Amakusa family has <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PowerCopying" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PowerCopying">Archer</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheAce" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheAce">Pyrrha</a> and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CreepyGood" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CreepyGood">Alice</a>. Its hard to determine on which family <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PlayingWithFire" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PlayingWithFire">Natsu</a> and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LastOfHisKind" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LastOfHisKind">Nippy</a> fit in, since Natsu, Alice and Nippy share dragon parents, but Natsu, Zeref and Morrigan share human parents</span>.</li><li> And finally there's the <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Fateburn family, that includes <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MasterSwordsman" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MasterSwordsman">Travis</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SnakePeople" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SnakePeople">Alysha</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChildProdigy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChildProdigy">Skyler</a> and Aisha. Skyler tells his half-brother <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChildByRape" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChildByRape">Jellal</a> that he will always have a place in the Fateburn family.</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BadassCrew" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BadassCrew">Badass Crew</a>: The Black Knights, Lelouch&#146;s guild subset and Team Lancelot, which is Suzaku&#146;s.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BattleStrip" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BattleStrip">Battle Strip</a>: Besides the usual with Gray (and Lyon), during their match Jeremiah and Elfman take off their shirts to show their <em>Manliness</em>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BeachEpisode" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BeachEpisode">Beach Episode</a>: Part of chapters 8 and 9, but it isn&#146;t what you&#146;d expect.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BeCarefulWhatYouWishFor" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BeCarefulWhatYouWishFor">Be Careful What You Wish For</a>: Two meta-examples back-to-back:<ul><li> For starters, many readers were vying for Erza to fight Cornelia during the Guild War arc, but after seeing the arc unfold, many wondered how Draconichero would pull it off without things feeling forced as hell. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Chapters 231 and 232 practically gut punched the entire fanbase by having VV unleash a spell that made all allies forget which side their on and only care about victory and the results are clear</span>. With how brutal some of these fights are getting, you get the feeling the creator is <img src="/images/article-hreficon-trivia.png" class="trivia1 rounded" title="This example contains a TRIVIA entry. It should be moved to the TRIVIA tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TrollingCreator" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TrollingCreator">taunting the fanbase for wanting such a thing</a>.</li><li> Fans have been outright demanding Lelouch go Dragon Force for arcs on end. Well, in chapter 232, we got it. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Except Lelouch is under VV's influence and this moment <em>clearly</em> isn't a moment of rejoicing, but rather a moment of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OhCrap" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OhCrap">"Oh, Shit!"</a> because Lelouch is clearly starting to become unhinged like his <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FutureMeScaresMe" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FutureMeScaresMe">evil self from the future</a></span>. Once again, you feel like Draconichero <img src="/images/article-hreficon-trivia.png" class="trivia1 rounded" title="This example contains a TRIVIA entry. It should be moved to the TRIVIA tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TrollingCreator" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TrollingCreator">is taunting us all</a>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BedmateReveal" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BedmateReveal">Bedmate Reveal</a>: In chapter 150, Gray wakes up and assumes his arm is asleep only it turns out to be Juvia under the covers. Overlaps with a case of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThereIsOnlyOneBed" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThereIsOnlyOneBed">There Is Only One Bed</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BelligerentSexualTension" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BelligerentSexualTension">Belligerent Sexual Tension</a>: Resolved between <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Rakshata and Lloyd</span> in chapter 161. It's still up in the air whether or not they're now a couple or if they were just engaging in rage sex.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigBadassBattleSequence" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigBadassBattleSequence">Big Badass Battle Sequence</a>: Most of the Envoy of the Future arc is one between the guilds of Fiore and Mordred's army of dragons and familiars.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigDamnHeroes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigDamnHeroes">Big Damn Heroes</a>: Happens to <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Guinevere</span> in chapter 38. First by <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Cornelia</span> and then by <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Schneizel, Rena, Asura, AND Erza</span>.<ul><li> Happens during the fight against Zero, the leader of Oracion Seis, as <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Makarov and Marianne</span> show up to bail out our heroes.</li><li> Gino becomes this in the Edolas arc to Wendy, Lelouch and Kallen</li><li> Happens during the Nirix arc where it looks like Kagura is about to bite the dust <img src="/images/article-hreficon-ymmv.png" class="ymmv1 rounded" title="This example contains a YMMV entry. It should be moved to the YMMV tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LikeYouWouldReallyDoIt" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LikeYouWouldReallyDoIt">(not really)</a> and <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Jellal</span> and Rorix show up to save her and the gang from Nirix.</li><li> During the Envoy From the Future arc, <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeelFaceTurn" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeelFaceTurn">Cobra</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VillainousRescue" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VillainousRescue">Emma</a> and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RememberTheNewGuy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RememberTheNewGuy">Leaf Valentine</a></span> all come to the heroes' aid.<ul><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">During the very following chapter, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DarkestHour" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DarkestHour">just as all hope seems lost</a> <em>Future Natsu</em> takes this trope <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UpToEleven" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UpToEleven">Up to Eleven</a> with a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DynamicEntry" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DynamicEntry">grandstanding entrance</a> and an epic punch to Mordred's face</span>.</li></ul></li><li> While not precisely heroes, the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ProfessionalKiller" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ProfessionalKiller">Garou Knights</a> show up to help Phoenix Grave against Cracked Gemstone.</li><li> Lucy keeps ending up on the receiving end of this trope in chapter 224. By no means is she as close to death as some other examples, but she seems to have the devil's luck getting helped out by allies whenever she starts to get in a pinch. In fact, this trope remains persistent with Lucy on the receiving end throughout the Guild War arc. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">At least until Bismarck and Ushiora come into play. By the time help does arrive, Lucy has long since passed out from fatigue</span>.<ul><li> By that same token, counting every instance this trope comes into play in the Guild War arc would take too damn long.</li></ul></li><li> An epic one in chapter 236 when <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Irene Berserion descends onto the battlefield in dragon form and not only heals Erza's injuries, she <em>injures</em> <strong>Acnologia</strong>. She then proceeds to kill VV.</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigDamnKiss" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigDamnKiss">Big Damn Kiss</a>: In chapter 76, <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Schneizel</span> presents one to <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Guinevere</span>.<ul><li> In chapter 146 you have one between <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Kagura and Jellal</span></li><li> Chapter 147 almost completely overshadows that one by finally resolving the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnresolvedSexualTension" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnresolvedSexualTension">Unresolved Sexual Tension</a> between <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Erza and Lelouch</span> with this trope. Both this example and the previous one overlap with <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HollywoodKiss" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HollywoodKiss">Hollywood Kiss</a> given the passion that's described as per the narration.</li><li> Chapter 153 ranks up <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Gray and Juvia</span> to <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OfficialCouple" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OfficialCouple">Official Couple</a> status with one of these and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DidTheyOrDidntThey" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DidTheyOrDidntThey">it's implied</a> that they made snoo-snoo at the end of the chapter(they didn't).</li><li> Chapter 163 does the same with <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Sherry and Lyon</span> after the latter finally understood the former's feelings.</li><li> In chapter 188 <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Pyrrha downright makes out with Skyler</span> after the latter tells her not to die a pointless death. Mortal danger is one hell of an aphrodisiac.</li><li> Chapter 220 has a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DoubleSubverted" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DoubleSubverted">double subversion</a>. First, it looks like it's about to be this trope with <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Suzaku and Minerva</span> only for it to turn into an <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AlmostKiss" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AlmostKiss">Almost Kiss</a> when they get interrupted. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Only for Suzaku to then bring this trope back into play by going all the way.</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BitchInSheepsClothing" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BitchInSheepsClothing">Bitch in Sheep's Clothing</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Rushio Seam</span>.<ul><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">The same with Monique A. Fiore</span>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BittersweetEnding" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BittersweetEnding">Bittersweet Ending</a>: The Rise to Power arc ends like this. Depending on your viewpoint, Sabertooth winning the Grand Magic Games over Serpent's Heart could feel like a downer. Kagura also finds out that Zangetsu and <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Jellal</span> are one in the same person <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">and has a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroicBSOD" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HeroicBSOD">mental breakdown</a>, but this gets amended and eventually the two move past it. Nivea dies. And Minerva finds herself, at the end of the arc, once again alone</span>. It's only this trope and not a complete <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DownerEnding" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DownerEnding">Downer Ending</a> like the Black Knights arc because of the hope brought about by the Kagura/Zangetsu ordeal.<ul><li> The same can be said of the Envoy of the Future arc. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Sure, Mordred's been defeated and the dragons return to their own timeline, but several members of many guilds, including Master Bob, are dead. The threat of Tartaros and Acnologia continues and Lelouch and Erza now know what would happen to Lelouch if he ever lost her.</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlackComedy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlackComedy">Black Comedy</a>: This exchange between Lelouch and Schneizel<div class="indent"> <strong>Lelouch:</strong> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MurderIsTheBestSolution" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MurderIsTheBestSolution">It would&#146;ve been faster to just kill them</a>.</div><div class="indent"> <strong>Schneizel:</strong> And what pray tell would you have liked me to have done with the bodies?</div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlackDudeDiesFirst" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlackDudeDiesFirst">Black Dude Dies First</a>: The first non-OC fatality in the whole series is <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Ren Akatsuki</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BookEnds" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BookEnds">Book-Ends</a>: Chapter 1 ends with Lelouch accepting Kallen into Knightmare Frame with the latter clutching his hand to "seize her destiny". Chapter 238 ends with <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Kallen doing the same for Ayame Futaba, thus bringing Kallen's character arc to a close</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BoxingLessonsForSuperman" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BoxingLessonsForSuperman">Boxing Lessons for Superman</a>: Natsu's <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TrainingFromHell" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TrainingFromHell">Training from Hell</a> in the Return of Fairy Tail arc seems to revolve around this given Chandra's exposition.<ul><li> The same could be said of his training with Enna Elsa.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BreakingTheFourthWall" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BreakingTheFourthWall">Breaking the Fourth Wall</a>: <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BunnyEarsLawyer" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BunnyEarsLawyer">Gino</a> makes a comment about how sarcasm needs its own font and not having one will confuse the readers.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BreatherEpisode" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BreatherEpisode">Breather Episode</a>: Chapter 220 helps the reader calm down from the action that had been going on in chapters prior, being full of lighthearted comedy and hijinks.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BrickJoke" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BrickJoke">Brick Joke</a>: In chapter 36, Cornelia tries to cure Gray of his stripping habit. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FailureIsTheOnlyOption" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FailureIsTheOnlyOption">This goes about as well as one would expect</a>. This trope comes into play when her first attempt to cure Gray involves <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ItMakesSenseInContext" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ItMakesSenseInContext">showing him a picture of</a> <img src="/images/article-hreficon-ymmv.png" class="ymmv1 rounded" title="This example contains a YMMV entry. It should be moved to the YMMV tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Squick" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Squick">Natsu in a Speedo</a>. When Gray later strips down after she tries duct tapping his clothes to his body, Gray is wearing a speedo instead of boxer shorts. And <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChekhovsBoomerang" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChekhovsBoomerang">then</a></em> during a debate later in the chapter over posters for the upcoming play, Tohdoh's idea is <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ItMakesSenseInContext" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ItMakesSenseInContext">Jeremiah wearing a speedo</a>.<ul><li> During the Naval Battle Jeremiah wears a speedo.</li><li> The author <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LampshadeHanging" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LampshadeHanging">lampshades</a> the use of this trope in chapter 48 by tossing a brick into orbit saying that that will make sense in about a hundred chapters.<ul><li> The brick hits him on the head at the end of chapter 161 making this a literal example of this trope, but also because Lelouch and Erza once again get kicked out of a restaurant for beating up a sleaze bag trying to grope the <em>exact same waitress</em> from chapter 48.</li></ul></li><li> Lucy being <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MissedTheCall" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MissedTheCall">absent</a> from the Edolas arc.</li><li> In the first chapter of the Yawgmoth Island arc, Sherry mentions that she wouldn't trust Gino with her pet goldfish. Gino points out she doesn't have a goldfish. In the last chapter of the arc, it's implied said goldfish were eaten by Angelica.</li><li> After the first battle of the Guild War arc, Lucy mentions that the council is going to get a bill <em>from</em> Fairy Tail this time given how many times they've sent bills to Makarov's desk for Fairy Tail's wanton destruction. The last chapter of the guild war arc shows that, yes, Lucy was completely serious.</li><li> Waaaaaaaaaay back in chapter 89, Margaret stated that she wanted to make Rustyrose her jester because he amuses her so. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Cut to 237 where he <em>is</em> a jester, but to Morrigan, not Margaret</span>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BridalCarry" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BridalCarry">Bridal Carry</a>: In the Nirix arc, this is how Hibiki rescues Princess Hisui.<ul><li> Archer carts Alice off the battlefield during the Grand Magic Games this way because she's exhausted, but she's acting like she's fine. Bonus points for the fact that Alice is his actual bride.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BringMyBrownPants" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BringMyBrownPants">Bring My Brown Pants</a>: Airy wets herself at the sight of one of Kalina's Nightmares. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Sorano</span> of all people, admits she peed herself in the aftermath of <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Kallen and Mirajane's battle.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BringMyRedJacket" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BringMyRedJacket">Bring My Red Jacket</a>: Subverted. Lelouch hates to get his red jacket mangled, damaged or torn since it was a gift given to him by Erza Scarlet so while he takes it everywhere, he always takes it off before things get rough. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnstoppableRage" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnstoppableRage">God help you</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BerserkButton" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BerserkButton">if you do somehow damage it</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BullyingADragon" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BullyingADragon">Bullying a Dragon</a>: Iron Star was pretty much asking for the gruesome BEATDOWN that ensued when they pissed Kallen off and subsequently got <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CurbStompBattle" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CurbStompBattle">curbstomped</a> by Marianne. At <em>what point</em> did antagonizing <em>Kallen</em> seem like a good idea?<ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SmallNameBigEgo" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SmallNameBigEgo">Audrey Belladona</a> also couldn't keep her <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SirSwearsALot" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SirSwearsALot">mouth</a> shut and attack Amy in front of Kallen, dragging her team into a fight. As Sting lampshades it, they were <em>slaughtered</em> like sheep.</li><li> Ushiora <em>really</em> should have known better than to try and murder Kalina to get a fight with <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MamaBear" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MamaBear">Kasumi</a>. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CurbStompBattle" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CurbStompBattle">Kasumi showed her</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoHoldsBarredBeatdown" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoHoldsBarredBeatdown">why that was</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoBodyLeftBehind" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoBodyLeftBehind">a bad idea</a>.</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CallBack" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CallBack">Call-Back</a>: In chapter 76, Erza repeats the exact same lines to Lelouch that he told her eight years ago to cheer her up <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">in order to help Lelouch get over his mother's death</span>.<ul><li> There's one to the very first chapter in chapter 114. Kallen says to Lelouch, almost word for word chapter one's end quote.</li><li> When Lelouch is having <em>yet another</em> mental breakdown, Erza snaps him out of his funk again, this time using the words he used to help her back in chapter 92.</li><li> Legretta still <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoodleIncident" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoodleIncident">isn't allowed anymore strawberry sunrises</a>.</li><li> Gino also worries about what they do to guys <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Bishonen" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Bishonen">like him</a> in <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PrisonRape" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PrisonRape">prison</a>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CallForward" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CallForward">Call-Forward</a>: During the flashback of Cornelia&#146;s history, Nonette talks about potentially becoming a Wizard Saint.<ul><li> During a flashback of <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Sindel's</span> history, Mavis talks about building a clubhouse for the Fairy Tail women that she was going to call Fairy Hills.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CaptainErsatz" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CaptainErsatz">Captain Ersatz</a>: Because fanfiction.net only allows stories where two series can be crossed over, the writer employs this trope to get a lot of characters from other series involved in all but name the same way the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/CodeGeass" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/CodeGeass">Code Geass</a> characters are involved. While some original characters are simply <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Expy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Expy">similar rather than identical</a>. The following are basically the same character. To wit:<ul><li> From Fighting Spirit:<ul><li> Rorix Graymare, Chandra Graymare, and Vanessa Graymare are <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/EndlessFrontier" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/EndlessFrontier">Haken Browning, Aschen Brodel, and Kaguya Nanbu</a>.</li><li> Selina Victoria, Renji Blake, Vixie Blake, and Leaf Valentine are <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/ProjectXZone" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/ProjectXZone">Saya, Reiji, Xiaomu and Sheath</a>.</li><li> Orochi Bahn, Shimon Ikari and Chikara Rasenhime are <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/TengenToppaGurrenLagann" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/TengenToppaGurrenLagann">Kamina, Simon, and Nia Tepplin</a>.</li><li> Juren Rakkan is <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/MahouSenseiNegima" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/MahouSenseiNegima">Jack Rakan</a>.</li></ul></li><li> From Serpent's Heart:<ul><li> Shura Sunshine and Henry Ichifira are <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/FireEmblemAwakening" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/FireEmblemAwakening">Tharja and Henry</a>.</li><li> Miala and Maria Hauticlere borrow appearance and personality from <a class="createlink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FireEmblemShadowDragon" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FireEmblemShadowDragon">Minerva and Maria</a>, though with Miala often drove to her <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RageBreakingPoint" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RageBreakingPoint">Rage Breaking Point</a> due to <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheThingThatWouldNotLeave" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheThingThatWouldNotLeave">Nippy's behavior</a>. However, the dynamic duo between the two that <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CharacterDevelopment" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CharacterDevelopment">eventually happens</a>, bring Miala to the status of dragon rider, like how Minerva is in her canon.</li><li> Ryumia Tatsumiya is so blatantly <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/MahouSenseiNegima" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/MahouSenseiNegima">Mana Tatsumiya</a> that the writer didn't even bother changing her last name or <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeaponOfChoice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WeaponOfChoice">Weapon of Choice</a>.</li></ul></li><li> Nocturnal Falcon and Frozen Jaguar's main group, with the exception of Sakura Menjou, are all based on the characters from Night Raid and the Jaegers from <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/AkameGaKill" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/AkameGaKill">Akame ga Kill!</a>.</li><li> Phoebe Amethyst and Sabrina Sapphire are <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/HyruleWarriors" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/HyruleWarriors">Cia and Lana</a> with Cia's obsession with Link replaced by Phoebe's obsession with <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MyHeroZero" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MyHeroZero">Zero</a>.</li><li> Howling Wolf, in addition to having Sayoko on the team, brings us Kyle Regent, Elizabeth Saturn and Lucas Senshiro. Or, in other words, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TalesOfVesperia" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TalesOfVesperia">Yuri Lowell, Judith, and Flynn Scifo</a>.</li><li> This was outright <em>invoked</em> with regards to Cracked Gemstone so that the author could get a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WholePlotReference" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WholePlotReference">Whole Plot Reference</a>. Ember Garnet, James J. Teakwood, Vanilla S. Chocolate, Cain Bloodstone, Jade Juniper, and Platinum Stardust are all <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WebAnimation/RWBY" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WebAnimation/RWBY">Cinder Fall, Roman Torchwick, Neo, Adam Taurus, Emerald Sustrai, and Mercury Black</a>. The only <em>real</em> change is that Cain is a machina where as Adam Taurus is a faunas.</li><li> Related to the above, Phoenix Grave gives us Wanda Rose, Legretta Upton, Heidy Orenstein, and Clarice Spay as iterations of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WebAnimation/RWBY" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WebAnimation/RWBY">Team RWBY</a>. And Pyrrha Amakusa, Nancy Abaddon, and Jin Tobias are Pyrrha Nikos, Nora Valkyrie, and Lie Ren.</li><li> Among the Rune Knights we have:<ul><li> Phelia Blendy and Senshiro Izanami as <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Naruto" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Naruto">Sakura and Sasuke</a>.</li><li> Amber Celadon as <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/BlazBlue" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/BlazBlue">Noel Vermillion</a>.</li><li> Kurena Menjou as <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/KillLaKill" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/KillLaKill">Ryuko Matoi</a>.</li><li> Adrian Bluecorn as <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Freezing" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Freezing">Arnett McMillan</a>.</li></ul></li><li> Atarella Kozuki, Enna Elsa, Alysha Fateburn and Travis Fateburn are Granberia, Alipheese Fateburn the 16th, Alma Elma, and Luka from <em>Monster Girl Quest</em>.</li><li> Tristan is this of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/LeagueOfLegends" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/LeagueOfLegends">Gnar</a> from the orange fur down to the growth issues.</li><li> The new council members are quite obviously this to <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/Danganronpa" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/Danganronpa">Byakuya Togami, Kyoko Kirigiri, Makoto Naegi and Chiaki Nanami</a>, while a new recruit for the Black Knights is based on Celestia Ludenberg.</li><li> One of the interviewees of the Neo Black Knights is based on <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/FateZero" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/FateZero">Kiritsugu Emiya</a>.</li><li> Lisa, Max and Ellie Heartfilia are <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Videogame/PokemonSunAndMoon" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Videogame/PokemonSunAndMoon">Lusamine, Gladion and Lillie</a></li><li> Marin Reverse is <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/Slayers" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/Slayers">Lina Inverse</a></li><li> If a character isn't listed here, then it's because they only resemble the character they're based on and are listed below under Expy.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CerebusSyndrome" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CerebusSyndrome">Cerebus Syndrome</a>: The Sindel arc starts off with a cheerful and lighthearted march across Fiore with Fairy Tail all gung ho on a group mission. The arc starts to take a <em>much</em> darker turn once the dark guild Frozen Jaguar makes an appearance. And it only got worse from there.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChekhovsGun" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChekhovsGun">Chekhov's Gun</a>: Though in this case it might as well be more Chekhov's location given all the buildup in the Unistrad arc regarding Krune Pass. According to <img src="/images/article-hreficon-trivia.png" class="trivia1 rounded" title="This example contains a TRIVIA entry. It should be moved to the TRIVIA tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WordOfGod" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WordOfGod">Word of God</a> the entire Unistrad arc is chock full of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChekhovsGun" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ChekhovsGun">this trope</a> and highly subtle <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Foreshadowing" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Foreshadowing">Foreshadowing</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ClothesMakeTheSuperman" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ClothesMakeTheSuperman">Clothes Make the Superman</a>: The asterisk system much in the same fashion as where <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/BravelyDefault" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/BravelyDefault">it's inspired from</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CreatorInJoke" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CreatorInJoke">Creator In-Joke</a>: The Drunken Spartan in chapter 1. On <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Website/DeviantArt" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Website/DeviantArt">DeviantArt</a> the author belongs to a group called the Drunken Spartans.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CoitusUninterruptus" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CoitusUninterruptus">Coitus Uninterruptus</a>: See <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InterruptedIntimacy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InterruptedIntimacy">Interrupted Intimacy</a> below, the second example.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ColdBloodedTorture" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ColdBloodedTorture">Cold-Blooded Torture</a>: Zero almost always tortures his targets before killing them, usually beginning with a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GroinAttack" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GroinAttack">Groin Attack</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ColonyDrop" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ColonyDrop">Colony Drop</a>: In a flashback regarding how <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ForegoneConclusion" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ForegoneConclusion">Angel&#146;s Feather became Fighting Spirit</a> the dark guild Demon&#146;s Horn drops <em>the moon</em> onto Earth Land. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Awesome/FairyWithoutWings" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Awesome/FairyWithoutWings">Rakkan throws it back into orbit</a></span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CooldownHug" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CooldownHug">Cooldown Hug</a>: Gino gives one of these to Anya during the Yawgmoth Island arc after <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Anya turns full dragon as a result of being <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BrainwashedAndCrazy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BrainwashedAndCrazy">Brainwashed and Crazy</a> and tries to <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MurderTheHypotenuse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MurderTheHypotenuse">kill Chelia</a></span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CombatPragmatist" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CombatPragmatist">Combat Pragmatist</a>: In the X788 Grand Magic Games, Hibiki, Miala and Anya all do this in rapid succession during Hunt:<ul><li> Using archive magic, Hibiki changes Miala's path, forcing her to take more time to get to her goal because of a single road block he added. This was ruled as <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LoopholeAbuse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LoopholeAbuse">Loophole Abuse</a> since nothing in the rules specified he wasn't allowed to do that.</li><li> Miala has Nippy run down a zigzagging path as he pushes off the walls with his hind legs, which again is rendered a case of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LoopholeAbuse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LoopholeAbuse">Loophole Abuse</a> since nothing in the rules said she couldn't do that.</li><li> Realizing she's going to lose in a contest of raw speed, Anya attacks Rogue outright and even though she knew he was going to dodge, it makes up all the difference to net her third place in the event.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CrapsackWorld" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CrapsackWorld">Crapsack World</a>: It seems to be a requirement of Knightmare Frame that you have some sort of sad history to be allowed into the guild.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CruelAndUnusualDeath" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CruelAndUnusualDeath">Cruel and Unusual Death</a>: Lelouch&#146;s Spinal Tap ability desegments the cartilage from your spinal column and leaves you in pieces. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThereIsNoKillLikeOverkill" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThereIsNoKillLikeOverkill">Overkill</a> much?<ul><li> That pales in comparison <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EveryoneHasStandards" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EveryoneHasStandards">by Lelouch's own admission</a> to the death of <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Ivan Dreyar</span>. Imagine being turned into a tree, but instead of it happening instantaneously, you feel every single moment of it in pure agony as your bones break into twigs and leaves and your body stretches to become made of wood. You can't see, hear <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AndIMustScream" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AndIMustScream">or talk</a>, but you can still feel pain. Then, someone chops you up into pieces <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThereIsNoKillLikeOverkill" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ThereIsNoKillLikeOverkill">and then</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KillItWithFire" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KillItWithFire">burns your pieces</a>. That is messed up.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CurbStompBattle" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CurbStompBattle">Curb-Stomp Battle</a>: CC, Ratatosk and Loke do this to a trio of demons in the Journey to Hell arc. CC even does it twice.<ul><li> Ratatosk Vs Ein. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Ein never stood a chance</span>.</li><li> Kyouka Vs The Black Knights. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Our heroes never stood a freaking <em>chance</em></span>.<ul><li> In the previous chapter <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">members of Fairy Tail get utterly wasted by the Black Knights</span>.</li></ul></li><li> Serpent's Heart going up against Crow's Nest, especially when Nessa ups the ante by going Dragon Force.</li><li> Chandra does this to Jace during the Grand Magic Games arc. She even interrupts the hammy intro that is declared before every fight. Poor bastard never stood a chance.</li><li> Gajeel Vs Zero, yes <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/CodeGeass" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/CodeGeass">that one</a>. Poor Gajeel never stood a chance. Granted this was before he finished his <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TrainingFromHell" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TrainingFromHell">Training from Hell</a> after Fairy Tail was <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FishOutOfTemporalWater" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FishOutOfTemporalWater">left behind in time</a>, but still...</li><li> Zelda<span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">/Ultear</span> Vs Dorothea Ernst in the Grand Magic Games. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Dat Arc of Time yo!</span></li><li> Philosopher's Stone in general has been getting this treatment <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">on the receiving end</span> throughout most of the Grand Magic Games. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AssholeVictim" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AssholeVictim">Probably for the best</a>.</li><li> Nonette vs <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Team Fairy Tail A</span> starts off this way with her <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">taking out Lucy and Lisanna with minimal effort right at the start</span>.</li><li> Alice vs Ember. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Ember never stood a chance.</span></li><li> The Rune Knights vs the <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">lesser members of Fairy Tail and Knightmare Frame</span>. The Rune Knights suffer a humiliating defeat.</li><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Atarella</span> vs Team Flamewing. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Skyler and his friends couldn't even scratch her</span>.</li><li> VV vs <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Irene Berserion</span>. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">VV ends as a bloodstain on the floor.</span></li><li> Serpent's Heart vs Enna Elsa. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">The results weren't <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DepravedBisexual" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DepravedBisexual">pretty for the mages</a>.</span></li><li> Sabertooth <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">ends up on the receiving end of this during chapter 248. Tartaros is clearly not to be taken lightly this time around</span>.</li><li> Fairy Tail <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"><em>finally</em> ends up on the <em>receiving</em> end of this when facing down the Zombie Squad</span>.</li><li> Chapter 254 takes this trope <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UpToEleven" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UpToEleven">Up to Eleven</a> with several instances of it back to back. First, the demon Letter goes solo against Kraken's Eye and promptly gets taken out quickly. Then, <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Ushiora takes to the field and wrecks all of Kraken's Eye, only for <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MamaBear" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MamaBear">Kasumi</a> to show up and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoHoldsBarredBeatdown" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoHoldsBarredBeatdown">utterly</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CurbStompBattle" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CurbStompBattle">wreck</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoBodyLeftBehind" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoBodyLeftBehind">her</a></span>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CurbStompCushion" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CurbStompCushion">Curb Stomp Cushion</a>: Though Eve tries during the Grand Magic Games against Lyon, he stands no chance and we are treated to one of the quickest fights in the arc.<ul><li> Fighting Spirit <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">performs marginally better than Sabertooth against Tartaros' initial attack force. Keyword there being <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KillEmAll" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KillEmAll">marginally</a></span>.</li><li> Fairy Tail <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">ends up on the receiving end of this while fighting, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheJuggernaut" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheJuggernaut">Roxanne</a>. Sure, Mira, Aquarius and Laxus get a few good hits in, but its ultimately futile. She kicks all of their asses, marking her <em>second</em> victory against the guild if one includes her one on one bout with Natsu</span>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DarkerAndEdgier" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DarkerAndEdgier">Darker and Edgier</a>: The series is a downplayed version of this for Fairy Tail. On the one hand, the author definitely does his best to bring up more adult subjects, but will still do things that are, as he puts it, true to Fairy Tail form. As for Code Geass, it's definitely <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LighterAndSofter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LighterAndSofter">Lighter and Softer</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DarkestHour" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DarkestHour">Darkest Hour</a>: Chapter 42. We have a lycan <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Kallen</span>, an <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BrainwashedAndCrazy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BrainwashedAndCrazy">evil</a> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Mirajane</span>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ObviouslyEvil" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ObviouslyEvil">suspicious vampires</a>, eternal night, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArtifactOfDoom" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArtifactOfDoom">cursed artifacts</a>, and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArsonMurderAndJaywalking" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArsonMurderAndJaywalking">worst of all</a>...a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LittleBitBeastly" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LittleBitBeastly">hairy</a> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LittleBitBeastly" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LittleBitBeastly">Lucy</a>.</span><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FramingDevice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FramingDevice">The quote</a> at the end of that chapter said it all</li></ul><div class="indent"> <em>The dreams are gone. Midnight has come. Darkness is our new kingdom.</em></div><ul><li> Chapter 100. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Margaret corrupts the Tenrou Tree&mdash;she makes it work for Grimoire Heart as opposed to Fairy Tail&mdash;and Erza is the only one within spitting distance of stopping her and is the only one with the power to do so that isn't preoccupied or unconscious</span>.</li><li> Not to be outdone by previous examples, chapter 191, appropriately titled Ultimate Despair, has the closest the series has come thus far to a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NearVillainVictory" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NearVillainVictory">Near-Villain Victory</a> and really brings about a sense of hopelessness and dread with even main characters looking like they're about to bite it <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">until <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigDamnHeroes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigDamnHeroes">Natsu comes from the future</a> [[Dynamic Entry and punches Mordred in the face</span>, once again sparking the light of hope in everyone]]. The narration even lampshades this example saying how just when things are at their darkest, light will eventually seep through.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ADayInTheLimelight" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ADayInTheLimelight">A Day in the Limelight</a>: The One Thousand and One Blades arc is this since it focuses on Kagura and Guinevere. The former hadn't even been introduced up until that point sans a single flashback and the latter is only a sub-main character compared to the likes of Lelouch, Kallen, Natsu and Erza.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeadPersonConversation" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeadPersonConversation">Dead Person Conversation</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Sachi appears before Kallen after Kallen wakes up in her flashback, but she&#146;s using Soul Projection in order to talk to Kallen one last time</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeathGlare" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DeathGlare">Death Glare</a>: It would be easier to count the amount of chapters when people <em>aren't</em> shot dirty looks.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DoesThisRemindYouOfAnything" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DoesThisRemindYouOfAnything">Does This Remind You of Anything?</a>: In chapter 48, Lelouch gives Erza a strawberry cheesecake that he made himself. Erza's thoughts on the taste? <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DoubleEntendre" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DoubleEntendre">The cheese is thick and creamy and she wants to savor the taste</a>. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SarcasmMode" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SarcasmMode">draconic hero is the master of subtlety as always</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Doorstopper" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Doorstopper">Doorstopper</a>: The series has almost eclipsed <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Fanfic/SoulChess" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Fanfic/SoulChess">Soul Chess</a></em> in length, which is already longer than all 7 Harry Potter books combined.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DownerEnding" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DownerEnding">Downer Ending</a>: The Black Knights arc ends this way. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Marianne dies. Suzaku gets to go to the council and becomes a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KarmaHoudini" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KarmaHoudini">Karma Houdini</a> for betraying Knightmare Frame. Several members of Knightmare Frame leave the guild and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PutOnABus" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PutOnABus">Lelouch leaves to go on a journey that will take him three to five years</a></span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DudeNotFunny" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DudeNotFunny">Dude, Not Funny!</a>: In-universe, when Suzaku is unable to access the Zantetsuken while he and Lelouch face down <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArcVillain" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArcVillain">VV</a>, Lelouch suggests if he should choke Minerva to death to get Suzaku to get angry to access the power. Suzaku becomes rather peeved at Lelouch for suggesting such a thing.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DynamicEntry" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DynamicEntry">Dynamic Entry</a>: Natsu breaks through an inn's roof to beat a wraith that gave Lucy a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JumpScare" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JumpScare">Jump Scare</a>.<ul><li> Which is nothing to compared to the one <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">his future self delivers where he jumps straight out of the time portal and punches Mordred in the face</span>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EnsembleCast" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EnsembleCast">Ensemble Cast</a>: While the members of Knightmare Frame and Fairy Tail get the main focus, characters from other guilds are also given some depth and a few even have their own story arcs, such as Kagura, Hibiki and Sherry and Lyon.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EurekaMoment" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EurekaMoment">Eureka Moment</a>: Lelouch has one when he realizes <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Nirix's</span> weakness.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EveryoneCanSeeIt" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EveryoneCanSeeIt">Everyone Can See It</a>: Kalina, Lucy, Mirajane and even possibly Jellal are already jumping on board with noticing that Lelouch and Erza might think of each other as more than <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlatantLies" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlatantLies">Just</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JustFriends" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JustFriends">Friends</a>. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Even when Lelouch and Erza do finally get together and try to hide it, Kallen and a few others are capable of seeing through the cracks</span>. This is example is actually hilariously averted by <img src="/images/article-hreficon-ymmv.png" class="ymmv1 rounded" title="This example contains a YMMV entry. It should be moved to the YMMV tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShippingGoggles" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShippingGoggles">Juvia</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Expy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Expy">Expy</a>: While there are plenty of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CaptainErsatz" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CaptainErsatz">blatant copies</a> of characters in this story, some only resemble the character their based on. Take note:<ul><li> Airy Kitsune borrows <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/LeagueOfLegends" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/LeagueOfLegends">Ahri's</a> looks, but Airy is <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheDitz" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheDitz">The Ditz</a> while Ahri is <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheVamp" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheVamp">The Vamp</a>.</li><li> Sindel <em>started</em> as a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CaptainErsatz" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CaptainErsatz">Captain Ersatz</a> of Syndra in her initial appearance, but with <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CharacterDevelopment" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CharacterDevelopment">Character Development</a> sinking in, she's more or less this. Not to mention Sindel's values system is way different given she grew up in Fairy Tail.</li><li> While Undine keeps up the pirate talk, her background and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TeamMom" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TeamMom">personality</a> make her too distinct to do anything more than resemble <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/EndlessFrontier" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/EndlessFrontier">Anne Sirena</a>.</li><li> Kasumi is actually this of other works done by the same author.</li><li> Asura Kaimen may resemble <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TalesOfSymphonia" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TalesOfSymphonia">Kratos Aurion</a> in personality and appearance, but his other traits such as background and actions clearly contradict his counterpart.</li><li> As the writer has never played <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/ShiningForce" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/ShiningForce">Shining Force</a>, Rena Sianne only borrows Riemsianne La Ves' appearance and nothing more.</li><li> Alice and Archer are <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/FateApocrypha" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/FateApocrypha">Red Assassin and Shirou Kotomine</a>. However, the goals of both and actions taken by them make them far more of good people than their counterparts. Also, Alice's...<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AmbiguousDisorder" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AmbiguousDisorder">behavior</a> is definitely different from Semiramis'.</li><li> Priscilla Starkwing was created with the idea of being <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TalesOfSymphonia" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/TalesOfSymphonia">Presea Combatir</a>, but older in terms of appearance and her personality is nothing like Presea's.</li><li> Jace Highwind and Leana Verundum from Kraken's Eye borrow appearances from <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/MagicTheGathering" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/MagicTheGathering">Jace Beleren and Liliana Vess</a>. However, Jace is a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CasanovaWannabe" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CasanovaWannabe">Casanova Wannabe</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ButtMonkey" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ButtMonkey">Butt-Monkey</a>, while Leana is decisively far less evil and interested in necromancy. In addition, Nessa Revenati is Nissa Revane.</li><li> While her sister Kurena blatantly rips off Ryuko, Sakura Menjou more or less simply resembles <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/KillLaKill" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/KillLaKill">Satsuki Kiryuin</a>.</li><li> From the Rune Knights:<ul><li> Bolt Naikara and Peshkatz Fireman are this of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MetalGearRisingRevengeance" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MetalGearRisingRevengeance">Raiden and Jetstream Sam</a>.</li><li> Judas Crossbolt is this of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Bleach" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Bleach">Yhwach</a> and Tony Wolfe is Coyote Stark.</li><li> Saigara Daishogu resembles <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Inuyasha" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Inuyasha">Sesshomaru</a>.</li><li> Sean Exodus borrows his appearance and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WarriorPoet" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WarriorPoet">Warrior Poet</a> nature from <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/FinalFantasyVII" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/FinalFantasyVII">Genesis Rhapsody</a>.</li><li> Siegfried Karn resembles <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/FateApocrypha" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/FateApocrypha">Saber of Black</a>.</li><li> Yamato Hayabusa's powers and appearance are borrowed from <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/AsurasWrath" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/AsurasWrath">Asura</a>, but he is <em>way</em> to calm to be everyone's favorite <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheBerserker" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheBerserker">Berserker</a>.</li></ul></li><li> With how much he lays an utter beating on our heroes and never utters a word, how could Nirix be this trope of anyone other than <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/TheDeathOfSuperman" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/TheDeathOfSuperman">Doomsday</a>? He's only not a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CaptainErsatz" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CaptainErsatz">blatant copy</a> given his powers work completely differently and he has a completely different background.</li><li> Isabella <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Belserion</span> is based on <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/BlazBlue" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/BlazBlue">Tsubaki Yayoi</a>, but time will tell if her story is similar.</li><li> Any character not listed here is likely a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CaptainErsatz" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CaptainErsatz">Captain Ersatz</a>. Please carefully consider which is which before adding an entry to this trope or the other one.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FailureIsTheOnlyOption" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FailureIsTheOnlyOption">Failure Is the Only Option</a>: Regarding <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">stopping Marianne's execution</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FantasticRacism" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FantasticRacism">Fantastic Racism</a>: With a side order of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HumansAreTheRealMonsters" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HumansAreTheRealMonsters">Humans Are the Real Monsters</a>. Undine's adoptive dragon parent, Erubay, hated humans to the point of stopping Undine from trying to marry one by killing him right in front of her. She only made an exception for Undine because when she found Undine as a tiny baby, Undine wasn't scared of her and gave her a hug. For Erubay, she's a bit justified considering that humans broke her wings and rendered her incapable of flying, which is why she spends all of her time in the ocean and she has lived for so long that her ideology seems to reflect that of Zeref's in regards to seeing how disgusting human culture can be.<ul><li> According to <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WordOfGod" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WordOfGod">Word of God</a> humans are this way towards demons, but this is sort of a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JustifiedTrope" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JustifiedTrope">Justified Trope</a> in-universe given how many demons trick and kill humans. Of course, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MySpeciesDothProtestTooMuch" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MySpeciesDothProtestTooMuch">Ratatosk would have a few things to say about this</a>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AFateWorseThanDeath" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AFateWorseThanDeath">A Fate Worse Than Death</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">C.C. basically lobotomizes Esmie Jufendissimo by erasing all her memories using Geass, rendering <strong>Ankhseram's Curse</strong> neutral. Niyoko finds it disturbing.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FemmeFatale" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FemmeFatale">Femme Fatale</a>: Selina Victoria from the dark guild Demon's Horn. The narration even describes her as one.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FightingYourFriend" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FightingYourFriend">Fighting Your Friend</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">A direct result of the Mass Hysteria caused by VV during the Guild War arc. The first wave of battles we see, and many were offscreen, include Erza Vs Cornelia, Wendy Vs Chelia, and Natsu Vs Gray. And there's still Natsu Vs Erza to come</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ForegoneConclusion" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ForegoneConclusion">Foregone Conclusion</a>: Suzaku's arc provides a flashback where we know the ending of the story will end with <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Juren Rakkan giving up his Wizard Saint status and Angel's Feather becoming Fighting Spirit due to the guild disbanding</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Foreshadowing" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Foreshadowing">Foreshadowing</a>:<ul><li> Milly&#146;s own family issues foreshadow similar issues in Cornelia&#146;s own arc.</li><li> Kallen also mentioned when she once used Breaker X in one of the earlier chapters. In chapter 9 we learn why she was scared of the technique previously.</li><li> We know that Kallen&#146;s third guild died because she lost control of her powers. We get to see how in chapter 9.</li><li> During Cornelia&#146;s flashback it&#146;s already been established that her darling older sister, Estellise, is going to die at some point. We're just waiting for the other shoe to drop as it were. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/FairyWithoutWings" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TearJerker/FairyWithoutWings">Oh god does it not make things any less heartwrenching when said shoe drops though</a>.</li><li> If you&#146;re paying attention you should be able to see the twist that <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Selina is Suzaku&#146;s <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MissingMom" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MissingMom">Missing Mom</a></span> coming.</li><li> <img src="/images/article-hreficon-trivia.png" class="trivia1 rounded" title="This example contains a TRIVIA entry. It should be moved to the TRIVIA tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WordOfGod" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WordOfGod">Word of God</a> is that the ending quote of chapter 44 is Foreshadowing of a later arc and it should be pretty obvious at this point that Mary Markov is <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Edolas Marianne</span>.<ul><li> And now we know why <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Suzaku betrayed Knightmare Frame</span>.</li></ul></li><li> In hindsight, it becomes obvious that draconichero was building towards <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Sindel being the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigBad" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BigBad">Big Bad</a> of her arc</span> the whole time, but you don't really know that the first time reading it.</li><li> Sindel <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">regaining part of her memory and having a portion of her seal undone in the battle against Rustyrose</span> should come as a shock to no one given how much it was discussed during the arc.</li><li> Chikara's true nature <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">and subsequently the true nature of Shimon's magic</span> was subtly hinted at when she drank Chandra and Orochi under the table <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">being a spirit, she would logically not be able to get drunk</span>.</li><li> Asura Vs Kagura in general was hinted at twice before it actually happened later in the arc.</li><li> True to form, draconichero was about as subtle as a hammer with regards to something bad going to happen to Nivea and/or in general at the end of the Rise to Power arc. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Nivea dies at the end of the arc</span>.</li><li> All of the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TemptingFate" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TemptingFate">Tempting Fate</a> talk of Erza dying throughout the Grand Magic Games arc was building up to <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Erza's death in Mordred's timeline</span>.</li><li> There's a moment way earlier on in the story where Lelouch talks about that he would never mess with a magic that he didn't fully comprehend <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">and look what happens when he dicks around with <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PowerCopying" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PowerCopying">Skeleton Key</a></span>.</li><li> The reveal that <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Morrigan and CC are the same person</span> has been hinted at for a long time. Let us count the ways:<ul><li> In chapter 2, CC is initially shown with a witch hat and working with a cauldron<span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">, likening her to the historical Morgan le Fay, a powerful witch and sorceress</span>.</li><li> Despite being a main character, CC isn't part of the Oracion Seis arc. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Brain who had met her before likely would've been able to identify her immediately</span>. And there's also the fact that CC <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">is identical to Morrigan in appearance</span>.</li><li> Eventually it becomes apparent that <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">CC's backstory is a lie given that Ushiora is a demon and therefore doesn't have an extended family. Leading one to wonder where she came from</span>.</li><li> Coupled with the above, <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">CC has Geass: Rewrite, which has bailed Lelouch's ass out of the fire from the council during his early Zero career. And it's apparent she uses it to keep up any guise that suits her</span>.</li><li> It is apparent that <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Morrigan likes to hide herself among Fiore as different people like Leyla Lazuli and Sephiria Gilgamesh. Cynthia "CC" Caroline is just another alias</span>.</li><li> During the Guild War, CC shows exactly what she's capable of <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">far beyond what even Lelouch knew her to be capable of, meaning there's far more to her than there appears to be</span>.</li><li> It also explains why <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Morrigan appears in chapter 74 to chase away Kyouka from the Black Knights and then CC pops up with nary a mention of Morrigan</span>.</li><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">CC and Morrigan are never on screen together</span>.</li><li> <em>Most damning of all</em> however, has to be the fact that CC knows every single Geass and notes that, far as she knows, no other human has mastered Geass beyond 7 spells. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Naturally, given she IS Morrigan, she would be capable of knowing all the spells she invented</span>. And <em>no one</em> caught this.</li></ul></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FramingDevice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FramingDevice">Framing Device</a>: At the beginning and end of each chapter the author provides a quote that falls in line with the context of the chapter. The quote can either be said by a character from the story from <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/CodeGeass" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/CodeGeass">either</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FairyTail" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FairyTail">fandom</a>, an original character, and even some already existing ones.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GenerationXerox" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GenerationXerox">Generation Xerox</a>: Many note that Natsu is very similar to his dragon parent Igneel in terms of personality.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GetARoom" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GetARoom">Get a Room!</a>: Kingsley suggests this of Laqueenta and Jackal given how much the two <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LikeAnOldMarriedCouple" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LikeAnOldMarriedCouple">start bickering</a> in chapter 248. Both resent the idea.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GilliganCut" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GilliganCut">Gilligan Cut</a>: In chapter 107 Bisca says she's ready for anything after she protected her guild in the absence of Tenrou's group. Cut to her <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ScreamingBirth" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ScreamingBirth">giving birth</a> to Asuka.<ul><li> In chapter 209 Murasaki tells Natsu and Lisanna the three things you <em>don't</em> do when dealing with horned rock bears. Next scene she's screaming at Natsu for doing all three things while they're being chased by rock bears.</li></ul></li><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GoOutWithASmile" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GoOutWithASmile">Go Out with a Smile</a></span>: Sachi</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GracefulLoser" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GracefulLoser">Graceful Loser</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Gemini when Suzaku defeats it while under the contract of Angel</span>. A few matches in the Grand Magic Games end this way too.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HalfTheManHeUsedToBe" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HalfTheManHeUsedToBe">Half the Man He Used to Be</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Tiberius</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HiddenInPlainSight" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HiddenInPlainSight">Hidden in Plain Sight</a>: Morrigan seems to thrive on this trope given she has disguised herself as Sephiria Gilgamesh and Leyla Lazuli while only changing her hair and eye color so as not to be found out. But her face, body proportions and voice are all unchanged. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Lelouch and the others never even fathomed that she could be their pizza loving comrade, CC</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HopeSpot" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HopeSpot">Hope Spot</a>: Oh so you think that just because Lucy <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">stopped Withengar's curse</span> before <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">the blood of 100 werewolves and 1 demon got onto Withengar's dagger</span> things are fine? <strong>WRONG!</strong><ul><li> Chapter 75. Surely draconichero wouldn't <em>really</em> kill off Marianne right? <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">See previous answer</span>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HorribleJudgeOfCharacter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HorribleJudgeOfCharacter">Horrible Judge of Character</a>: A downplayed example with Arcadios in the Nirix arc. When doing open recruitment to help solve the murder mystery going on during the arc, he tells Lelouch he's free to do anything if it means solving the case. Lelouch jokes <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlackComedy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BlackComedy">in his usual fashion</a> that the wrong people might take that to start kidnapping virgins and sacrificing them to their gods. Arcadios then employs that he thinks himself to avert this trope not realizing her just let <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VigilanteMan" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VigilanteMan">Zero</a></em> into the imperial palace and gave him free reign to do as he pleased.<ul><li> People think this of Toma with regards to his relationship with VV.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HumansAreTheRealMonsters" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HumansAreTheRealMonsters">Humans Are the Real Monsters</a>: Discussed at length throughout the Tartaros arc and seems to be the stance that the guild of demons takes throughout it. Most of its members, even Jackal, have been mistreated by humans and it has shaped, in turn, their hatred of humans as a result. It doesn't help that humans take demons as a case of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AlwaysChaoticEvil" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AlwaysChaoticEvil">Always Chaotic Evil</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HumiliationConga" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HumiliationConga">Humiliation Conga</a>: Happens to <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BreakTheHaughty" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BreakTheHaughty">Audrey Belladona</a>. First she's utterly beaten by Kallen for attacking one of her teammates, later Sting sucker punches her in the face for trying to pin the blame on him. She's then submitted to Jiemma's <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShamefulStrip" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShamefulStrip">Shameful Strip</a> and expelled from Sabertooth. When she becomes a dark mage intending to join Cracked Gemstone, Legretta <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoHoldsBarredBeatdown" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoHoldsBarredBeatdown">beats the tar out of her</a> for traumatizing Wanda and nearly killing Clarice, then she's sent to prison. And finally Clarice convinces her to give her information about Cracked Gemstone, which reveals that Audrey was on death row at the time. She only gets off it because Clarice put in a good word for her. Fortunately things seem to go her way the next time she's seen in the Guild War arc, having learned it from fellow prisoner Lilianna Vergamon, but time will tell if the author is done <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CosmicPlaything" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CosmicPlaything">toying with her yet</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InSpiteOfANail" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InSpiteOfANail">In Spite of a Nail</a>: Despite the introduction of Serpent's Heart and <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">making Jellal a member of their guild</span>, Sabertooth still becomes the strongest guild in Fiore in Fairy Tail's absence by winning the Grand Magic Games.<ul><li> Hell, in spite of Tenrou Island being delayed a year, Acnologia still sinks it to the bottom of the ocean and Grimoire Heart still invades prior to that.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InterruptedIntimacy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InterruptedIntimacy">Interrupted Intimacy</a>: In chapter 95, on Tenrou Island, both Freed and Mirajane inadvertently find Loke and Airy <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PrimalScene" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PrimalScene">already engaged in the act</a>.<ul><li> This happens to <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Rakshata and Lloyd</span> in chapter 161, though to be fair they had the door locked and Sherry opened it with magic. They were only bothered because they were being loud. After the interruption, neither one stops and they <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CoitusUninterruptus" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CoitusUninterruptus">keep going</a>.</li></ul></li><li> <img src="/images/article-hreficon-ymmv.png" class="ymmv1 rounded" title="This example contains a YMMV entry. It should be moved to the YMMV tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ItWasHisSled" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ItWasHisSled">It Was His Sled</a>: If you are at all familiar with the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/CodeGeass" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/CodeGeass">Code Geass</a> mythos then <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Zero and Lelouch turning out to be the same person</span> shouldn&#146;t be much of a spoiler.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JackBauerInterrogationTechnique" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JackBauerInterrogationTechnique">Jack Bauer Interrogation Technique</a>: The members of Knightmare Frame will do this to yield results if they think it will help.<ul><li> Lelouch is shown doing this to the guildmaster of Hedgehog Claw.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JerkWithAHeartOfGold" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JerkWithAHeartOfGold">Jerk with a Heart of Gold</a>: The Celestial Spirit Vul may annoy and even belittle Yukino at times, but like the other spirits, she has her best interests at heart.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JumpScare" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JumpScare">Jump Scare</a>: Poor Lucy gets one of these in chapter 41.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JustEatHim" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JustEatHim">Just Eat Him</a>: How <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Ratatosk</span> disposes of <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Ein</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JusticeByOtherLegalMeans" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JusticeByOtherLegalMeans">Justice by Other Legal Means</a>: Even though Jiemma was testified against by his guild members, he was arrested for assaulting an officer of the council, namely Suzaku rather than abusing his guild, which we all know he's guilty as sin of.<ul><li> Suzaku has attempted this on VV time and again, with absolutely no success, only further cementing Lelouch's opinions on the blond that <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MurderIsTheBestSolution" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MurderIsTheBestSolution">Murder Is the Best Solution</a>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KarmaHoudini" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KarmaHoudini">Karma Houdini</a>: Averted in so far. Knightmare Frame makes <em>damn</em> sure all their enemies get the beating you want them to...unless you&#146;re name is <img src="/images/article-hreficon-ymmv.png" class="ymmv1 rounded" title="This example contains a YMMV entry. It should be moved to the YMMV tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LawfulGood" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LawfulGood">Suzaku</a>.<ul><li> However, Knightmare Frame themselves sort of get away with manslaughter when it comes to Kallen's berserk rampage early on in the series.</li><li> Suzaku is seen as this for his <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">betrayal of the guild. Some people are so outraged by this, you would think he is solely responsible for Marianne's death as though he executed her himself</span>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KillerRabbit" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KillerRabbit">Killer Rabbit</a>: Ratatosk. His etherious form is a squirrel.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KissingUnderTheInfluence" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KissingUnderTheInfluence">Kissing Under the Influence</a>: During a private conversation in Sabertooth's hotel suite, Minerva starts having one too many glasses of red wine and starts to get tipsy. She then leans towards <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Suzaku</span> and lips are locked <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">followed by a case of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CoitusEnsues" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CoitusEnsues">Coitus Ensues</a>, but then it's revealed that everything after a certain line of dialogue was <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllJustADream" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AllJustADream">part of a very vivid dream Minerva was having</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SubvertedTrope" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SubvertedTrope">since she passed out after another glass of wine and all the saucy bits of the scene were all in her head</a></span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KnightOfCerebus" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KnightOfCerebus">Knight of Cerebus</a>: By <img src="/images/article-hreficon-trivia.png" class="trivia1 rounded" title="This example contains a TRIVIA entry. It should be moved to the TRIVIA tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WordOfGod" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WordOfGod">draconichero's admission</a> the Unistrad arc is the darkest he is willing to go <em>without</em> killing anyone. So apparently things can <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FromBadToWorse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FromBadToWorse">still get worse</a>. This, of course, begs the question, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ParanoiaFuel" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ParanoiaFuel">how dark is he willing to go when a body count is involved</a>? And, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnyoneCanDie" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnyoneCanDie">given</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Fanfic/TalesOfBleachUnrealSociety" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Fanfic/TalesOfBleachUnrealSociety">previous</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Fanfic/SoulChess" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Fanfic/SoulChess">works</a> who will die?<ul><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">These questions are answered by the Nirix arc and the Envoy of the Future arc</span>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KnowWhenToFoldThem" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/KnowWhenToFoldThem">Know When to Fold Them</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">The first battle of the Guild War ends with Lelouch checkmating Suzaku by sending <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheAce" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheAce">Nonette</a> to face Suzaku. Knowing that alone he can't defeat her, orders to retreat, leaving several fights unfinished.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LetsYouAndHimFight" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LetsYouAndHimFight">Let's You and Him Fight</a>: The very basis of all of the battles in the Guild War arc after chapter 232.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LoadsAndLoadsOfCharacters" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LoadsAndLoadsOfCharacters">Loads and Loads of Characters</a>: Not only both original series have lots of characters, with the Expies and Ersatz of other series, the number can easily reach over one hundred.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LoveTriangle" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LoveTriangle">Love Triangle</a>: Lelouch can&#146;t seem to avoid being caught in one, can he? Both Kallen and Shirley have it out for him and he's implied to have an interest in Erza. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">As of 147, Erza has officially claimed him</span>.<ul><li> As of the events that lead to Suzaku <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">becoming guild master of Sabertooth</span> he is now caught in one between <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Minerva and Yukino</span>.</li><li> Jellal is currently caught in one with Ultear and, of all people, Kagura. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">As of 146, he's dating Kagura</span>.</li><li> In the Nirix arc, Hisui has caught the eye of both Rolo and Hibiki. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">And at the end of the arc she takes a liking to Hibiki</span>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MamaBear" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MamaBear">Mama Bear</a>: Every mother in this story is an asskicker of some variety that can and <em>will</em> beat your ass into next Tuesday if you inflict bodily harm upon their children. Even surrogate parents, like how Undine is for Mermaid Heel, act this way. Kasumi in particular takes this trope <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UpToEleven" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UpToEleven">Up to Eleven</a> with how much Kalina's well-being means to her. Of course, she, Nessa, <em>and</em> Alice have all shown their foes the kind of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CurbStompBattle" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CurbStompBattle">payment you get</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TooDumbToLive" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TooDumbToLive">for messing with their children</a>. Margaret of course, remains the sole exception who could not give less of a shit about her son <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Jellal</span>. Hell, even canon moms that weren't this trope have somehow become this trope <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EstablishingCharacterMoment" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EstablishingCharacterMoment">Isn't that right, Irene</a>?</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MassOhCrap" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MassOhCrap">Mass "Oh, Crap!"</a>: Pretty much the reaction&mdash;reader included&mdash;when <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Acnologia</span> shows up in chapter 31 <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">same for his appearance in chapter 235</span>.<ul><li> All of Fairy Tail also has this reaction when they realize Nonette is <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Gildarts'</span> rival.</li><li> Knightmare Frame has this reaction when they realize they're gonna have to fight <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">three of the four Gods of Ishgar (who have been brainwashed).</span></li></ul><div class="indent"><strong>Rivalz:</strong> We're so screwed.</div><div class="indent"><strong>Amy:</strong> Thank you <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CaptainObvious" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CaptainObvious">Captain Obvious</a>.</div></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MeaningfulEcho" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MeaningfulEcho">Meaningful Echo</a>: The line that Lelouch uses to snap Erza out of her funk in chapter 92, is later used by Erza on <em>him</em> at the end of the Cracked Gemstone arc to do the same. See <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CallBack" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CallBack">Call-Back</a> above.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MoodWhiplash" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MoodWhiplash">Mood Whiplash</a>: The range of emotions and tones for scenes throughout the same <em>chapter</em> can range from hilarious to downright tragic or even terrifying, sometimes back to back.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MirrorMatch" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MirrorMatch">Mirror Match</a>: Suzaku when he faces off against Gemini who is currently his spitting image. In fact, every time Gemini sees use, it usually results in this trope.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MookHorrorShow" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MookHorrorShow">Mook Horror Show</a>: The Black Knights certainly invoke this, especially Kallen, aka the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RedBaron" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RedBaron">''Crimson Nightmare''</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MundaneMadeAwesome" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MundaneMadeAwesome">Mundane Made Awesome</a>: Chess has never sounded so interesting than when Lelouch and Lucy face off.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MurderIsTheBestSolution" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MurderIsTheBestSolution">Murder Is the Best Solution</a>: Often the topic of debate in this fic.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MyFriendsAndZoidberg" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MyFriendsAndZoidberg">My Friends... and Zoidberg</a>: During the Yawgmoth Island arc, because Ayaka is the party's client and not a mage of the guild, the narration constantly refers to the group as "The mages of Lamia Scale, plus Ayaka."</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MySpeciesDothProtestTooMuch" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MySpeciesDothProtestTooMuch">My Species Doth Protest Too Much</a>: According to Ratatosk, not <em>all</em> demons were created by Zeref, many were already around before Zeref ever came into existence and seek to coexist with humans. It shouldn't be too hard to understand <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AlwaysChaoticEvil" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AlwaysChaoticEvil">why that's a problem</a>. <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HalfHumanHybrid" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HalfHumanHybrid">Kasumi's birth</a> marked a step in the right direction and Ratatosk even pulled a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TheLionKing1994" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TheLionKing1994">Rafiki</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MythologyGag" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MythologyGag">Mythology Gag</a>:<ul><li> Chapter 1 would not be the first time we&#146;ve seen Kallen in a playboy bunny suit.</li><li> Chapter 1 is also almost a play by play of Natsu&#146;s meeting with Lucy. We have a guildless mage, a dragonslayer who rescues her and a douchebag pretending to be said dragonslayer who then gets the tar beaten out of him.</li><li> Some of the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FramingDevice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FramingDevice">quotes</a> are often used this way.</li><li> In a flashback Jeremiah can be seen wearing an Orange jacket.</li><li> Inoue herself is this to the Inoue in <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Fanfic/SoulChess" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Fanfic/SoulChess">Soul Chess</a></em>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Fanfic/SoulChess" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Fanfic/SoulChess">Kasumi</a> can't seem to avoid being <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MadeASlave" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MadeASlave">Made a Slave</a> can she?</li><li> Suzaku gets bit by Arthur the cat.</li><li> Mordred himself pays perfect homage to <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">the embodiment of what Lelouch was when he enacted Zero Requiem</span><ul><li> You also have <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Shirley</span> dying at the hands of <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Rolo</span> during the timeline Mordred is from, which is <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">one of the catalysts that set Lelouch off in canon</span>.</li></ul></li><li> Monica's <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Angel name</span> is Florence, like her Knightmare Frame in the manga.</li></ul></li></ul></div><p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder1');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Tropes N to Z&nbsp;</div><div id="folder1" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;"><ul><li> <img src="/images/article-hreficon-trivia.png" class="trivia1 rounded" title="This example contains a TRIVIA entry. It should be moved to the TRIVIA tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NamesTheSame" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NamesTheSame">Name's the Same</a>: Oracion Seis' leader and Lelouch's alter ego are both Zero.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoHoldsBarredBeatdown" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoHoldsBarredBeatdown">No-Holds-Barred Beatdown</a>: It is <em>clear</em> that Kalina can't hold a candle to Ushiora and Ushiora makes it known.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoodleIncident" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoodleIncident">Noodle Incident</a>: Something happened with Nonette and a steamroller that Lelouch referred to as a horror story.<ul><li> Also whatever happened on the X783 trip to Fighting Spirit.</li><li> Also, apparently something happened with <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PersonOfMassDestruction" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PersonOfMassDestruction">Natsu</a>, golf and go-karts that he was worried the council found out about.</li><li> According to Cornelia and Kallen, the days CC served as advisor were dark days. Lelouch takes their word for it.</li><li> Legretta is not allowed anymore strawberry sunrises.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoSell" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoSell">No-Sell</a>: Mage Hunter Werewolves have anti-magic fur so they completely negate caster magic used on them. The same cannot be said for holder magic as Cornelia is all too quick to point out. However, <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">The werewolves just then <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoSell" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoSell">No-Sell</a> the holder magic for reasons yet to be explained, but are terrifying enough as it is that they're no selling attacks from Erza Scarlet and Cornelia</span>.<ul><li> Characters will sometimes do this to their opponents in combat against certain magic attacks either by deflecting or shielding against them.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ObliviouslyEvil" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ObliviouslyEvil">Obliviously Evil</a>: <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TinyTyrannicalGirl" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TinyTyrannicalGirl">Fresa</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SpoiledBrat" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SpoiledBrat">Jagoda</a> didn't know the "Familiars" she was summoning weren't magical beings from another dimension, but people who were teleported from their homes, and she wasn't aware she was enslaving them, until Lelouch pointed it out.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PayEvilUntoEvil" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PayEvilUntoEvil">Pay Evil unto Evil</a>: If you are a member of the Black Knights, you believe in this.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ParentalAbandonment" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ParentalAbandonment">Parental Abandonment</a>: In Kallen's, Schniezel's and Guinevere's case and maybe a few others we don't know about too.<ul><li> <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Kallen's been subverted as her <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MissingMom" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MissingMom">Missing Mom</a> is now part of Knightmare Frame</span>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PetTheDog" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PetTheDog">Pet the Dog</a>: When Kinana comes staggering out of the forest with <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EyeScream" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EyeScream">her eye shot out</a> from her fight with Cornelia and Natsu as Cubellios, she hoarsely says she's thirsty. Lahar is the one to give her some water even though he was bound to arrest her.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PleasePutSomeClothesOn" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PleasePutSomeClothesOn">Please Put Some Clothes On</a>: Lelouch to Milly whenever her <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VoluntaryShapeshifting" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VoluntaryShapeshifting">Voluntary Shapeshifting</a> leads to a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WardrobeMalfunction" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WardrobeMalfunction">Wardrobe Malfunction</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PostHumousCharacter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PostHumousCharacter">Post Humous Character</a>: Estellise Heurassein.<ul><li> Charles Vermillion.</li><li> Subverted with <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Atarella Kozuki</span>.</li><li> Travis Fateburn<span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">, Jellal and Skyler's father</span></li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PowerGivesYouWings" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PowerGivesYouWings">Power Gives You Wings</a>: Many mages have spells or transformations that allows them to fly. Even Lyon lampshades that now <em>everyone</em> can fly.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PowerOfTheVoid" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PowerOfTheVoid">Power of the Void</a>: Cyax, the Void Dragon, <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">is Mordred's strongest minion and the only dragon <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NotBrainwashed" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NotBrainwashed">Not Brainwashed</a>.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PrisonRape" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PrisonRape">Prison Rape</a>: When Jellal whose mental state in this series is trapped eight years in the past because his mind did not progress due to his brainwashing&mdash;long story&mdash;doesn't know what a prison bitch is, Cobra tells him not to drop the soap.<ul><li> When <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShouldersOfDoom" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShouldersOfDoom">Arcadios</a> and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TopHeavyGuy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TopHeavyGuy">Neppa</a> come by Blue Pegasus' group to ask for Hibiki's aid during the Nirix arc and drag him away without explanation, Eve misreads the situation and tells Hibiki not to drop the soap at all costs. Jenny, bless her soul, realizes that Eve is <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ComicallyMissingThePoint" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ComicallyMissingThePoint">way off the mark</a>.</li><li> Done again in a later chapter of that same arc when Hibiki asks Orochi if he has any idea what they do to <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Bishonen" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Bishonen">guys like him</a> in prison.</li><li> Mentioned once more in the Cracked Gemstone arc when Audrey Belladonna sells out her cellmate for cigarettes, and the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SeenItAll" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SeenItAll">Warden</a> tells one of her subordinates to find her following the raping sounds.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PromotedToParent" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PromotedToParent">Promoted to Parent</a>: Naoto after the death of his and Kallen&#146;s mother and their father abandoned them.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OddFriendship" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OddFriendship">Odd Friendship</a>: Knightmare Frame and Fairy Tail are, on some belief systems, as different as night and day, but the protective way they treat their nakama is why they are on such good terms.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OfficialCouple" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OfficialCouple">Official Couple</a>: In order of being cemented in the fanfic, we have: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Jellal and Kagura, Lelouch and Erza, Gray and Juvia, Hisui and Hibiki, Lyon and Sherry, Isamu and Chandra, Skyler and Pyrrha, Laxus and Mirajane, Suzaku and Minerva, Sting and Yukino, Kent and Inoue and Shirley and <em>Max</em> of all people</span>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OurWerewolvesAreDifferent" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OurWerewolvesAreDifferent">Our Werewolves Are Different</a>: The entirety of the Unistrad arc.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RatedMForManly" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RatedMForManly">Rated M for Manly</a>: Pretty much any male member of Fighting Spirit is this.<ul><li> Jeremiah Vs Elfman takes this <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UpToEleven" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UpToEleven">Up to Eleven</a>. It's even lampshaded by the phrase "The manliest thing you've ever seen"</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ReplacementGoldfish" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ReplacementGoldfish">Replacement Goldfish</a>: A literal example in chapter 8. Lelouch goes out to buy his sister a new goldfish before she realizes her old one had gone and done the surface belly flop.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RunningGag" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RunningGag">Running Gag</a>: If an Exceed is in Suzaku's presence, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MythologyGag" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MythologyGag">chances are</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnimalsHateHim" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnimalsHateHim">it will bite him</a>.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SailorEarth" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SailorEarth">Sailor Earth</a>: This is a Fairy Tail fanfic, something like this was inevitable. New guilds have sprouted up, including the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/CodeGeass" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/CodeGeass">Code Geass</a> guild Knightmare Frame, but all <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OriginalCharacter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OriginalCharacter">Original Character</a> examples such as Frozen Jaguar and Revenant's Tomb are known to exist. Phoenix Grave is actually a case of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AscendedExtra" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AscendedExtra">Ascended Extra</a> and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OCStandIn" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/OCStandIn">O.C. Stand-in</a> since the guild <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShownTheirWork" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShownTheirWork">does exist</a> in canon with a character that has the same surname as Sabertooth's Minerva, but nothing is known about them beyond that.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ScreamsLikeALittleGirl" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ScreamsLikeALittleGirl">Screams Like a Little Girl</a>: Hibiki is mentioned to scream very girly. <em>Laxus</em> of all people screamed that way when he was <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MegatonPunch" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MegatonPunch">punched</a> by Chandra. Natsu lampshades it.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SerialEscalation" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SerialEscalation">Serial Escalation</a>: The battles on the final day of the Grand Magic Games are set up to be this and succeed in this regard.<ul><li> With a <img src="/images/article-hreficon-ymmv.png" class="ymmv1 rounded" title="This example contains a YMMV entry. It should be moved to the YMMV tab."><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ToughActToFollow" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ToughActToFollow">few</a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BreatherEpisode" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BreatherEpisode">exceptions</a> each arc itself tries to be this in scale and stakes.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ScrewTheRulesImDoingWhatsRight" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ScrewTheRulesImDoingWhatsRight">Screw the Rules, I'm Doing What's Right!</a>: <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">In chapter 217 Kagura, Kyle, Elizabeth, Xingke, Tianzi, Rakshata, and Sorano go against orders and side with Fairy Tail and Knightmare Frame.</span></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ScrewThisImOuttaHere" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ScrewThisImOuttaHere">Screw This, I'm Outta Here!</a>: Tiberius&#146; reaction when he sees Kallen with Lelouch.<ul><li> Platinum tries this too during the Cracked Gemstone arc, but that goes south <em>very fast</em>.</li></ul></li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SelfDeprecation" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SelfDeprecation">Self-Deprecation</a>: Alex Goldrose remarks that having <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VainSorceress" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VainSorceress">Guinevere</a> and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MsFanservice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MsFanservice">Jenny</a> duke it out in the Grand Magic Games was clearly motivated by someone thinking with their genitalia. Harmless at first until you realize this is the creator's <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AuthorAvatar" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AuthorAvatar">Author Avatar</a> talking, meaning the author fully acknowledges that what is being said is more than likely true.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SingleStrokeBattle" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SingleStrokeBattle">Single-Stroke Battle</a>: Asura Vs Kagura ends this way both times.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SleepCute" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SleepCute">Sleep Cute</a>: Natsu, Lisanna, and Happy in chapter 65. Erza even notes that if she had a blanket she would've covered them with one.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShaggyDogStory" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShaggyDogStory">"Shaggy Dog" Story</a>: The Cracked Gemstone arc ends this way. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile">Although Lelouch stopped Cracked Gemstone's plan, the person he needed to find, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MissingMom" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MissingMom">Farah Dreyar</a>, dies of a heart attack before he's able to ask her 